entations and random scaling (0.02–1) to avoid overfitting. Reward the policy when the classifier is correct or reaches ≥0.9 confidence within up to T=5 steps. The learned policy consistently improves accuracy over random and always-forward baselines as the number of moves increases across multiple data splits."}]}
